Help - Secure Logon








Help - Logon to the Secure Web Portal






First Time Log-on  Instructions (except users logging in through Exostar)

You must take two actions the first time you  access the portal.     

Change your temporary password.     

At the login screen, type in your UserID and  Password. Press "Submit".
You will be prompted to enter your current  password and select and verify a new password. Press "Submit"
 The  password must be 8 to 12 characters in length and contain at least one numeral  and one letter. 
The UserID and Password are case sensitive, so  be sure to remember whether you use upper or lower case letters.
A message will appear indicating your password  change was successful. Press the "Continue" button to display the  portal home page.


Select challenge and response pairs used for  verification when resetting passwords with the self-service password reset tool.  After login, you will be redirected to a page  where you can select five challenge questions and enter your responses.  Please take this opportunity to complete this  immediately. Otherwise, you will be redirected to this page every time you log  in until you do select your questions and provide responses.



Additional  Information

To Update Your Profile: Select the "Update  My Profile" link under the "My Account" heading. Select the  "Update Profile Information" link. From here, you may update:     

E-mail Address
Phone Number
Fax Number
Business Address


Password Changes: You may change your password  any time that you visit the portal home page. Select the “Change Password” link  under the "My Account" heading. Enter your current password, enter  your new password, confirm your new password, and press the “Submit” button. 
Password Expiration: Boeing security policy  requires that passwords be changed every 90 days. You can change it sooner if  you like. A notice will automatically remind you after 90 days. Passwords may  not be reused; therefore, you always need to enter a new one after the  expiration date. 
Password Reset: If you forget or lose your  password, please use the self-service password reset tool located on the portal  log-on screen. Press the blue button titled "Forgot Your Password?"  You may also call the Boeing Enterprise Help Desk 

These password reset tool will only  work if you have selected your challenge/response pairs for verification.
Authorized Public Key  Infrastructure (PKI or x.509 Certificate Users)

If your organization has a PKI agreement with  Boeing, your PKI certificate may be used to log in. The first time you use a  PKI certificate, you will be prompted to login using your User-ID and Password  so that your PKI certificate can be associated to your User-ID. If your  organization does not have a PKI agreement with Boeing, your browser will  report an error. If you receive an error, use your User-ID and Password to log  in.

To Get an Account

Contact your Boeing representative or the Boeing  focal who controls the information that you desire access to.

Obtain additional  help for accounts and password resets at the Boeing Enterprise Help Desk

Customers, partners, suppliers:  (425) 237-8000
Boeing employees: USA and  International callers dial (425) 234-0911
Boeing employees: USA only, toll  free (888) 469-0911

NOTE: International callers - USA  Country code is 1
Return to the Secure Access Welcome Page





Boeing: Defense Overview























Boeing









+share













Defense













Broad Expertise, Integrated Systems






Boeing’s expertise spans a broad range of products in defense.  Fighter jets, rotorcraft, embedded product support, cybersecurity  products, surveillance suites, advanced weapons, missile defense and  commercial aircraft derivatives all fit in Boeing’s portfolio. The company can leverage this holistic knowledge and deliver the value of  those integrated systems to its customers.








